data.description: Welcome to your charming two-story Painted Sky at Waterview home, where modern comforts meet suburban tranquility. From its inviting curb appeal to the lush backyard oasis, this home offers the perfect blend of elegance and functionality. Step inside to find a welcoming foyer with vaulted ceilings opening to the front office where abundant natural light abounds. The heart of the home lies within the kitchen, equipped with stainless steel appliances, a counter bar, single basin stainless steel sink with an adjoining dining area and walk-out to the back deck. The kitchen seamlessly flows into the living room with luxury vinyl plank flooring where you will find some of the best mountain views in the city. Upstairs, the primary suite boasts an attached 5 piece bath and generous closet space, while three additional bedrooms and a full bathroom provide ample accommodation for family and guests. Finishing out the upper living area is a loft, laundry room with folding counter bar and a full bath with an oversized counter. Make your way to the unfinished walk-out basement to discover additional bathroom rough in, framed bedroom and tons of space to finish out and make your own. The backyard is a lush retreat where you will find an oasis awaits with raised flower beds, storage shed, and over sized concrete patio perfect for entertaining. Located just off the Powers Corridor, this home provides easy access to schools, restaurants, shopping, and military bases, ensuring convenience and connectivity. With its thoughtful design, luxurious features, and desirable amenities, this home in Painted Sky at Waterview is more than just a place to live - it's a place to call home.
